<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Signal_processing" title=3D"=
Signal processing">signal processing</a>, <b>cross-correlation</b> is a <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Similarity_measure" title=3D"Similari=
ty measure">measure of similarity</a> of two series as a function of the di=
splacement of one relative to the other. This is also known as a <i>sliding=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dot_product" title=3D"Dot product=
">dot product</a></i> or <i>sliding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Inner-product" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Inner-product">inner-produc=
t</a></i>. It is commonly used for searching a long signal for a shorter, k=
nown feature. It has applications in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Pattern_recognition" title=3D"Pattern recognition">pattern recognition</=
a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_particle_analysis" titl=
