<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Time_delay_analysis">Time d=
elay analysis</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DCross-correlation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D17" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Time delay analysis"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Cross-correlations are useful for determining the time delay between two=
 signals, e.g., for determining time delays for the propagation of acoustic=
 signals across a microphone array.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-correlation#cite_note-12=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-correlation#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup clas=
s=3D"noprint Inline-Template" style=3D"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowra=
p;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify" =
title=3D"Wikipedia:Please clarify"><span title=3D"I doubt that this definit=
ion is used for microphone arrays, since it involves an integral over all t=
ime. Perhaps integration over a time-window? (May 2015)">clarification need=
ed</span></a></i>]</sup>  After calculating the cross-correlation between t=
he two signals, the maximum (or minimum if the signals are negatively corre=
lated) of the cross-correlation function indicates the point in time where =
the signals are best aligned; i.e., the time delay between the two signals =
is determined by the argument of the maximum, or <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Arg_max" title=3D"Arg max">arg max</a> of the cross-correlat=
ion, as in<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;=
"><math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle \tau _{\mathrm {delay} }=3D{\underset {t\in \mathbb {=
R} }{\operatorname {arg\,max} }}((f\star g)(t))}">
