t and output of a system with nonlinear dynamics can be completely blind to=
 certain nonlinear effects.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-SAB1_14-0" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-correlation#cite_note-SAB=
1-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup> This problem arises because some quadratic moments can eq=
ual zero and this can incorrectly suggest that there is little "correlation=
" (in the sense of statistical dependence) between two signals, when in fac=
t the two signals are strongly related by nonlinear dynamics.
</p>
